].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.einnews.com/pr_news/512477940/ksi-to-release-new-single-poppin-featuring-lil-pump-smokepurpp-on-march-27th|title=KSI to Release New Single, \u201cPoppin\u201d Featuring Lil Pump, Smokepurpp on March 27th|date=2020-03-23|website=EIN News|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-24}}</ref> It is the third single from KSI's upcoming 2020 debut album ''Dissimulation''. The song charted at number 43 on the [[UK Singles Chart]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/48106/ksi/|title=KSI full Official Chart History|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Official Charts Company]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>\n\n== Promotion ==\nOn 18 March 2020, KSI announced via social media that he would be releasing a new single in the next week, and on the same day, he posted the song's artwork to his social media pages, revealing that the song is titled \"Poppin\" and that it features Lil Pump and Smokepurpp.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite tweet|user=KSIOlajidebt|number=1244735326179950593|title=Got a big one for you #poppinchallenge|date=2020-03-18|access-date=2020-04-24|author=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet|user=KSIOlajidebt|number=1240344439651995654|title=Out next week lmao. Pre order/pre save now|date=2020-03-18|access-date=2020-04-24|author=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B94plYrAFBM/|title=Popping ft @lilpump and @smokepurpp Link in bio|last=|first=|date=2020-03-18|website=[[Instagram]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-24}}</ref> The song was made available for [[pre-order]] on the same day.\n\n=== \"Poppin challenge\" ===\nOn 30 March 2020, KSI announced via social media that he would be hosting a competition called \"#PoppinChallenge\". He asked people to record their own verses for \"Poppin\", and the best verse, decided by public vote, will replace Lil Pump's verse on a remix of the song which will appear on the deluxe edition of KSI's upcoming 2020 album ''Dissimulation''.<ref name=\":0\" /> On 17 April 2020, American YouTube rapper Crypt was announced as the winner of the competition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oMIRi2eTgb0|title=The Winner Of The Poppin Challenge Is...|last=|first=|date=2020-04-17|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QOCY2QC7AWY|title=I WON THE KSI POPPIN' CHALLENGE|last=|first=|date=2020-04-17|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insider.com/ksi-new-rap-music-poppin-youtuber-boxing-jake-logan-paul-2020-4|title=KSI conquered YouTube and boxing. Now, he wants to break the mold of 'YouTuber music,' and blow 'trash' musicians like the Paul brothers out of the water.|last=Tenbrage|first=Kat|date=2020-04-22|website=[[Insider Inc.|Insider]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>\n\n== Commercial performance ==\nThe song entered the UK Singles Chart at number 43. It dropped to number 56 the following week, before dropping out of the top 100.<ref name=\":1\" /> The song spent two weeks on the [[UK R&B Singles and Albums Charts|UK R&B Singles Chart]], peaking at number 23.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/r-and-b-singles-chart/20200410/114/|title=Official R&B Singles Chart Top 40|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Official Charts Company]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n== Music video ==\nAn audio visualiser video for the song was uploaded to KSI's [[YouTube]] channel on 26 March 2020. As of April 2020, it has 6 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GGLE8gk9fng|title=KSI - Poppin (feat. Lil Pump & Smokepurpp)|last=|first=|date=2020-03-27|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-24}}</ref> The music video, directed by TajvsJaj, was filmed in [[Los Angeles]] in March 2020 and was uploaded to KSI's YouTube channel on 3 April 2020, one week after the release of the song.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://grmdaily.com/video/ksi-poppin-lil-pump-smokepurpp|title=KSI Gives Visual Treatment To \"Poppin\" Featuring Lil Pump & Smokepurpp|last=|first=|date=2020-04-03|website=[[GRM Daily]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref> The music video stars Asian dancer Bailey Sok and features cameo appearances from American actor and comedian [[King Bach]] and two of the song's producers, Diego Ave and Mally Mall.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://grungecake.com/ksi-popping-lil-pump-smokepurpp/articles/65556|title=English rapper KSI enlists Lil Pump and Smokepurpp for 'Poppin'|last=|first=|date=2020-04-06|website=GRUNGECAKE|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref> As of April 2020, it has 7 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xa0qshcRhDQ|title=KSI - Poppin (feat. Lil Pump & Smokepurpp) [Official Music Video]|last=|first=|date=2020-04-03|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref> A [[Making-of|behind-the-scenes]] video of the filming of the music video was uploaded to KSI's YouTube channel on 10 April 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fmf_KsHjGC8|title=KSI - Poppin (feat. Lil Pump & Smokepurpp) [Behind The Scenes]|last=|first=|date=2020-04-10|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Digital download<ref name=autogenerated2 />\n| title1 = Poppin\n| note1 = featuring [[Lil Pump]] and [[Smokepurpp]]\n| length1 = 3:33\n| length6 = \n| length10 = \n| title10 = \n| length9 = \n| title9 = \n| length8 = \n| title8 = \n| length7 = \n| title7 = \n| length5 = \n| title6 = 