[[Mesopotamia]] and [[Kingdom of Armenia (antiquity)|Armenia]] by the [[Sasanian]] king [[Narseh]]. The battle took place between Carrhae and Callinicum and was a decisive victory for the Sasanians. \n\nGalerius and Tiridates escaped with a remnant of Roman forces to [[Antioch]].<ref>{{cite book |last1=Dupuy |first1=Richard Ernest |title=The Harper Encyclopedia of Military History: From 3500 BC to the Present |date=1993 |publisher=HarperCollins |isbn=978-0-06-270056-8 |page=175a |language=en}}</ref> Eutropius and Theophanes has recorded versions of a celebrated story regarding a public humiliation of Galerius by Diolectan.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Edwards |first1=Iorwerth Eiddon Stephen |last2=Gadd |first2=Cyril John |last3=Hammond |first3=Nicholas Geoffrey Lempri\u00e8re |last4=Boardman |first4=John |last5=Walbank |first5=Frank William |last6=Lewis |first6=David Malcolm |last7=Bowman |first7=Alan |last8=Astin |first8=A. E. |last9=Garnsey |first9=Peter |last10=Crook |first10=John Anthony |last11=Lintott |first11=Andrew William |last12=Cameron |first12=Averil |last13=Rawson |first13=Elizabeth |last14=Champlin |first14=Edward |last15=Rathbone |first15=Dominic |last16=Ward-Perkins |first16=Bryan |last17=Whitby |first17=Michael |title=The Cambridge Ancient History: Volume 12, The Crisis of Empire, AD 193-337 |date=1970 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |isbn=978-0-521-30199-2 |page=81 |language=en}}</ref> was trying to distance himselffrom the stigma of this defeat.\n\nDiolectan later sent reinforcements for Galerius, and the latter managed to defeat the [[Sassanids]] two years later at the [[Battle of Satala (298)]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Battles involving the Roman Empire|Carrhae]]\n[[Category:Battles involving the Sasanian Empire|Carrhae]]\n[[Category:Battles of the Roman\u2013Sasanian Wars|Carrhae 296]]\n[[Category:290s conflicts|Carrhae 296]]\n[[Category:296]]\n[[Category:History of \u015eanl\u0131urfa Province]]\n[[Category:3rd century in 